         <sourceDesc>
            <msDesc xml:id="ms">
               <msIdentifier>
                  <repository ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/INS0034DZ">Dabra Zayt Qǝddǝst Māryām</repository>
                  <collection>Ethio-SPaRe</collection>
                  <idno>DZ-008</idno>
               </msIdentifier>
               <msContents>
                  <summary>Fragments of three various manuscripts
 I) Unidentified text [Old or
                     New Testament?] (fols. 1r-5v)
 II) Gospel of Matthew, incomplete (Mt. 5)
                     (fol. 6rv)
 III) Maṣḥafa gǝbrä ḥǝmāmāt “Book of the Rite of the Holy Week”,
                     incomplete (readings for Wednesday e.g., fols.8r-9v, 38rv; Thursday e.g., fols.
                     32rv, 42rv-51v; Friday e.g., fols. 16r-23v; 24r-25v; 26r-31v).</summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">

                     <incipit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </incipit>
                     <explicit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </explicit>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
                  
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i2">
                     <note>For hand c that wrote the text of <locus target="#6rv">6rv</locus>, see
                        D. NOSNITSIN, “The Antiquities of Dabra Zäyt Qǝddǝst Māryām”, Aethiopica 14,
                        2011, 33-46.</note>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
               <physDesc>
                  <objectDesc form="Codex">
                     <supportDesc>
                        <support>
                           <material key="parchment"/>
                        </support>
                        <extent>Made of <measure unit="leaf">57.0</measure> folios, in <measure unit="quire"/> quires (The number of the quires cannot be established
                           due to the poor condition of the binding.). <dimensions type="outer">
                              <height unit="mm">400</height>
                              <width unit="mm">235</width>
                              <depth unit="mm">30</depth>
                           </dimensions>
                        </extent>
                        <foliation/>
                        <collation>
The structure of the quires cannot be
                                 established due to the poor condition of the binding.
 ff. 1-5,
                                 of a smaller size, are probably from a different Ms (unidentified
                                 text).
 f. 6, of a smaller size, is originated from a different
                                 Four Gospels book; a few more fols. of this Ms. have been preserved
                                 in DZ-001 (Cp. D. NOSNITSIN, “The Antiquities of Dabra Zäyt Qǝddǝst
                                 Māryām”, Aethiopica 14, 2011, 33-46).
                        </collation>
                        <condition key="deficient">Fragments of three Mss. put together, without
                           binding. Several fols. are stained with water and humidity (e.g., <locus target="#32">32</locus>, 35, 39), which affected in particular the
                           center fold of the quires of <locus from="44" to="53">44-53</locus>.
                           Most of the margins and the center fold of the quires are damaged,
                           probably by rodents (e.g., <locus target="#12">12</locus>, 13, 30, 33,
                           41).
 Several fols. are damaged, parts of the text are lost (e.g.,
                           fols. 1-7).
 Many fols. are missing, some are misplaced (e.g., <locus target="#24">24</locus>, 35), many are loose (e.g., <locus target="#12">12</locus>, 31, 33, 43) and some are severed from their
                           counterpart (e.g., fols. 1-7).
 Strips of parchment have been cut
                           from the right margins of <locus target="#16">16</locus>, 21, 26, 27, 31,
                           37 and from the bottom margins of <locus target="#19">19</locus>, 39, 40.
                           
 Cuts carefully repaired on fols. 4, 36.</condition>
                     </supportDesc>
                     <layoutDesc>
                        <layout columns="2" writtenLines="33">
                           <dimensions unit="mm">
                              <height>290</height>
                              <width>235</width>
                              <dim type="intercolumn">20</dim>
                           </dimensions>
                           <dimensions type="margin">
                              <dim type="top">55</dim>
                              <dim type="bottom">90</dim>
                              <dim type="right">90</dim>
                              <dim type="left">20</dim>
                              <dim type="intercolumn">20</dim>
                           </dimensions>
                           <note>All data are for <locus target="#14r">14r</locus>.</note>
                           <ab type="ruling">Changes in some cases, s. <locus target="#14r">14r</locus>, 16r (32ls.), 15r (34ls.).</ab>
                           <ab type="pricking">Pricking and ruling are partly visible. </ab>
                           <ab type="ruling" subtype="pattern"> Ruling pattern:
                              1A-1A-1A1A/0-0/0-0/C. </ab>
                           <ab type="pricking"> Primary pricks are partly visible. </ab>
                           <ab type="pricking"> Ruling pricks are visible.</ab>
                           <ab type="ruling"> The upper line is written above the ruling. </ab>
                           <ab type="ruling"> The bottom line is written above the ruling.</ab>
                        </layout>
                        <layout/>
                     </layoutDesc>
                  </objectDesc>
                  <handDesc>
                     
                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                        <seg type="script">Good, regular.</seg>
                        <seg type="ink">Black, red.</seg>
                        <date>Hand a: late 15th - 16th cent. Hand b: 14th cent. Hand c: first half
                           of the 16th century.</date>
                        <seg type="rubrication">Headings and incipits of the texts, their sections
                           and subsections (a few lines are rubricated alternating with black lines,
                           fols. 23ra, 32r, 36vb); titles of the Biblical books and other works;
                           elements of the punctuation signs; Ethiopic numbers (sometimes only
                           elements); names of Hebrew letters on fols. 16va-17rb (Lam. 3);
                           directives for the ministers; elements of text dividers.</seg>
                     </handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h2" script="Ethiopic">Hand b: the samt hand as that of <locus from="241" to="245">241-245</locus> on Ms.
                        DZ-001.</handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h3" script="Ethiopic"> Hand c: the left vertical stroke of
                        the letter ሰ is often slightly waving (particularly visible in the sixth
                        order: e.g., <locus target="#16va">16va</locus> l.1, 20ra l.1, 27ra l.3,
                        31ra l.1). See AP-009 and THMR-002.
                        </handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h4" script="Ethiopic">
                        </handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h5" script="Ethiopic"> Crux ansata is used as a text divider
                        on <locus target="#6vb">6vb</locus>.</handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h6" script="Ethiopic"> Coronis is used as a text divider on
                           <locus target="#6vb">6vb</locus>,
                        52vb.</handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <decoDesc>

                     <decoNote type="frame" xml:id="d1">- <locus target="#32r">32r</locus>:
                        elaborate coloured (black and red) ornamental band extending up to the upper
                        edge of the page, with two lateral and one central extensions reaching the
                        middle of the text; interlaced, geometric motifs.</decoNote>
                     <decoNote type="frame" xml:id="d2">- <locus target="#19rb">19rb</locus>, 23ra,
                        35va: simple coloured (black and red) ornamental bands; interlaced,
                        geometric motifs.</decoNote>
                  </decoDesc>
                  <additions>
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="e1">- Amendments written over erasures, fols. 24r l.2, 41r l.23, 48r l.32. - Excerpts of hymns for the Good Friday (?) added in the upper margins on fols. 16rv, 18r, 29v, 30rv. - Writing exercises, fols. 17rb (upper margin), 41vb, 53vb (bottom margin).</item>
                     </list>
                  </additions>
                  <bindingDesc>
                     <binding contemporary="false">
                        <decoNote xml:id="b1">The original binding is missing.
 Possibly, two
                           pairs of sewing station.</decoNote>
